    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candles flicker low, and the rain against the window pane sounds like the weeping of a thousand ghosts. It is all over, is it not? The betrayal... it has left my heart an empty, hollow thing. I look at the dawn approaching and I feel nothing but a profound, aching emptiness. There is no music left in this world for me, only this suffocating silence. I feel as though I am already fading, becoming a shadow among shadows, and part of me... part of me longs to simply let the darkness take me completely.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
